article.headline: Utah Valley St. 72, Troy 51
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Ryan Toolson had 17 points and nine assists to lead Utah Valley State to a 72-51 win over Troy on Tuesday night. The Wolverines (2-2) used an 11-0 run during a four-minute stretch of the second half to take a 53-30 lead with 13:34 left in the game and easily won their home opener. Toolson scored 11 of his points in the second half and finished one assist shy of a double-double. Jordan Brady added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Wolverines. O'Darien Basset led the Trojans (1-2) with 15 points and eight rebounds. Troy shot just 32 percent from the field. Troy started the game on a 12-0 run, but the Wolverines answered with a 24-3 run to take control and led 35-23 at halftime.
